<h5>
  How to idetify action-reaction pairs on free-body diagrams
</h5>
<ul>
  <li>
    Action-reaction pairs <em>always</em>
    appear on different free-body diagrams.
  </li>
  <li>
    Imagine that Mike punches Evander:
    <ul>
      <li>There is a force on Evander's free-body diagram whose agent is Mike</li>
      <li>There is a force on Mike's free-body diagram whose agent is Evander</li>
    </ul>
    These forces are an action-reaction pair.
  </li>
  <li>
    Action-Reaction pairs always have equal magnitude and opposite direction.
  </li>
  <li>
    <em>Every</em> force is part of a pair.
    Sometime's you don't see them because you don't draw every free-body
    diagram you can, but they are <em>always</em> there.
  </li>
</ul>

